        <p class="lead">GEORGE coordinating specialized agents across the automotive value chain.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Modern OEMs deal with complex, siloed processes. Orchestration ensures agents collaborate consistently across ISA-95 layers — from shop floor signals to enterprise planning.
        </p>

        <h2>Process</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Event (e.g., production delay) triggers orchestration.</li>
          <li>GEORGE routes the task to specialized agents (Root Cause, Supply Chain, Finance).</li>
          <li>Agents exchange context via shared memory and policies.</li>
          <li>Orchestrated response is logged, validated, and escalated if needed.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Breaks down silos between IT/OT.</li>
          <li>Ensures every agent follows the same governance rules.</li>
          <li>Speeds up decision-making by 30–50%.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
